Firstly, the lady who took my order actually forgotten my order when i'm sitting in the restaurant of less than 5 customers around.  (This is not the main point) 

Secondly, they served non-fresh food that landed my brother(11years old)  & my boyfriend in a 6days food poisoning. 
(What was worse is even 4pills of carbon for my brother did not help, & my boyfriend fainted the next day after we had the food). 

Thirdly, when my boyfriend called up domino's MY to ask for compensation. They were trying to find ways to shirk responsibility, apparently they failed so they (different personnel)  called back 3 times to ask if our food tasted weird. If it tasted weird we would alr have asked for exchange on the spot?? 
In the end, they said they could only compensate a set of what we had for the incident.. 

MAIN POINT: 
Guys, we paid rm77++ for this meal & have to pay in total of rm161 for my boyf's medical fees, & also of rm40 for my brother's medical fees. Additionally, he could not attend work & have to get a 5 days of unpaid leave. 

I was thankful that my brother is fully cured after 7days, you never know how bad food poisoning can impose on kids.. 

You shall weigh the price of having the pizza.. i'm never having domino's with the kind of food their serving & the way they are gonna shirk responsibilities, you never know if you land yourself in the hospital & you'll be surprised that they can only tell you they can only serve you their pizza again with the amount you have to pay for medical fees just to have their pizza.

Hi Domino's Pizza. On 3rd October 2016, at 6.38pm, we placed an online order of 1 Large Beef Pepperoni + 2 Wonda Kopi Tarik, 1 Classic Personal Pizza & 1 Fabulous Four (which consists of Mini Cinnadots + Cheesy Mozzarella Stix + Roasted Chicken Drummets + Garlic Cheese Onion Rings). The order was arranged to be collected at  Section 14, PJ outlet at 8.30pm. 

Not wanting to be late, my wife arrived at 8.20pm, and was told that the order was not ready. Seeing that she was early, she went to wait in the car and came back in at 8.35pm. She was informed it would take another 10 minutes. So she went back to her seat, and went back up to the counter at 8.42pm and it is still not ready. That is also when she saw our order was only placed into the oven. at 8.47pm, Both pizzas were removed from the oven at 8.49pm, She was then asked to change the cheese stix in the fabulous four to twisty bread. She refused and insist to get what we have ordered. The staff went behind the counter and appear again shortly after and asked my wife to change the mini cinnadots to something else. She was informed that those two items have not been prepared even though we placed our order at 6.35pm!! My wife again declined and still insist to have what we initially ordered. At 9pm, we finally received our order. When asked why we were asked to change so many items in the menu and we had to wait so long, your staff's reply was only  malam ni busy, banyak order. So after waiting for 40 minutes, my wife headed home and once we open the fabulous four, the Garlic Cheese Onion Rings were not there and was replaced by chicken popcorn (or something that looks like it), without being informed. 

So in conclusion, we made and order at 6.35pm, to be picked up at 8.30pm (almost 2 hours to prepare), got delayed by a solid half hour, and still get the wrong order. This is truly unacceptable as not only we wasted our time, which we would never get back, and could be better spent doing other things then to wait for our order to be ready, behind schedule, ultimately, we also did not receive what made us want to try the fabulous four in the first place, the Garlic Cheese Onion Rings without us being informed about it.

Sadly bad experience over and over again with Setia Alam branch. Called 1300888333 to order takeaway, told by phone that I can collect after 15mins. Went there after 15mins and waited more than 30mins! Waiting was bad, but worse of all was the bad customer service! 
1) no specific que system; those with receipts/ordered at the shop gets their pizzas first; they simply place the pizza boxes in no specific order
2) no one bothers that you stand in front of their cashier counter; they are too busy cracking jokes with colleagues in the kitchen
3) no apologies to all the customers who complaint; in fact they only can ask you to sabar la in a harsh tone
4) my 1st pizza was ready; but they misplace it and when my 2nd pizza was ready, I saw it getting cold while they figure out how to re cook or look for it; and didn't bother to redo my pizza until I asked
5) when asked to cancel the order; they just ignore you
6) when ask for store manager's name, they take 15mins to find his name; as if he is too afraid to admit he is in charge
7) some customers were given a voucher sorry we are late but I never got any.. In fact I never got any apology at all!
8) on coming home, I called 1300888333 hoping to give my feedback but they tell me the complaints dept is engaged and promised to call back but they never did!
Is it too much to ask that customers be treated well?
